<s> Dear World Wide Web Consortium,  </s>
<s> I have seen the term 'web site' and 'website' and 'web-site' used interchangeably in the industry and on your w3.org site.  </s>
<s> Can you tell me the w3.org stance on this term or direct me to an email resource who can answer this question?  </s>
<s> Thanks, Sara SARA CALLAHAN-SANTO | PROJECT DIRECTOR SARA.CALLAHAN-SANTO@ICROSSING.COM DIRECT: 480.505.5856  </s>
<s> WWW.ICROSSING.COM http://www.icrossing.com/  </s>
<s> NEW YORK CITY - SCOTTSDALE YOUR DIRECT SOURCE TO SEARCH AND A TOP 25 INTERACTIVE AGENCY (MEDIA MAGAZINE, 2003)  </s>
<s> W3C uses US English and the Chicago Manual of Style.  </s>
<s> They say "Web site" for formal writing and that "website" is fine for informal and friendly writing.  </s>
<s> I believe that in the UK "website" is one word and preferred, per the Oxford dictionaries.  </s>
<s> (see the section on Internet and Web) Hope this helps, Susan Lesch http://www.w3.org/People/Lesch/ World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) http://www.w3.org/  </s>
